hands_on_practices.solution:
Relevant equation:
$$D_A(R)=R\left(1-\frac{2M}{R}\right)^{-1/2}.$$
Differentiate with respect to $R$:
$$\frac{dD_A}{dR}
=\left(1-\frac{2M}{R}\right)^{-1/2}
+R\left(-\frac12\right)\left(1-\frac{2M}{R}\right)^{-3/2}
\frac{d}{dR}\left(1-\frac{2M}{R}\right).$$
Compute the inner derivative:
$$\frac{d}{dR}\left(1-\frac{2M}{R}\right)=\frac{2M}{R^2}.$$
Thus
$$\frac{dD_A}{dR}
=\left(1-\frac{2M}{R}\right)^{-1/2}
-\frac{R}{2}\left(1-\frac{2M}{R}\right)^{-3/2}\frac{2M}{R^2}
=\left(1-\frac{2M}{R}\right)^{-1/2}
-\frac{M}{R}\left(1-\frac{2M}{R}\right)^{-3/2}.$$
Setting $dD_A/dR=0$ gives
$$\left(1-\frac{2M}{R}\right)^{-1/2}
=\frac{M}{R}\left(1-\frac{2M}{R}\right)^{-3/2},$$
so
$$1-\frac{2M}{R}=\frac{M}{R}
\quad\Longrightarrow\quad
1=\frac{3M}{R}
\quad\Longrightarrow\quad
R=3M.$$
